Bytes: 465
To be honest I did not pay attention to this. But there is an issue with using `&&` and `||`. Somehow the `HSelect` optimization doesn't kick in and we end up with a series of `HIf` and constants. I haven't looked further. Maybe because there is no `HCondition` input to the `Hif` (they take directly a boolean value)?

But I *am* using `boolean` inputs instead of synthesizing conditions to avoid being short-circuited by `HSelect` and `HBooleanNot` optimizations.

